 coverage for proxy classes, which might not be ideal. I could design a test that programmatically uses Mockito's PluginSwitch to disable the default ProxyMockMaker and enable the inline option. But I need to consider if the resource exists and if it can be ignored. Maybe I should explore the mockito-inline dependency in Mockito 5, as it might contain the necessary extension resource while examining classpath order and plugin loading behavior.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_96Y69BkTWnQwcj6uDMIezmtr|fc_0bb659a3f93ff911016a21cfcefd0881969c879d8c175ffd5d", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/main/extracted/org/mockito/internal/configuration/plugins/PluginInitializer.java", "limit": 160}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/main/extracted/org/mockito/internal/configuration/plugins/PluginInitializer.java\",\"limit\":160}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 218, "output": 559, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25353, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780600766885, "responseId": "resp_0bb659a3f93ff911016a21cfbfeec8819690082d83bf184aa5"}}
